Looks like TexturePacker no longer respects TexturePacker.Settings.square when it's set to true.

It uses "square" when it does the layout. However when it goes to write the image:

TexturePacker.writeImages(...) - line 144

It only checks to make sure that the width and the height are a power of two, not that they are the same.

Need to add something along the lines of:

``` java
if (settings.square) {
    width = Math.max(width, height);
    height = Math.max(width, height);
}
```
